description.narrative:
Description of objectives and expected outcome of the project activities in concrete and measurable project outcomes
Specify whether the requested budget is in a proportionate relation to the nature, scale and envisaged results of the proposed project activities (do not use more than a page).
1.	To contribute to job creation for Syrian, Palestinian and Jordanian youth through supporting existing (M)SMEs (50 per cent) and start-ups (50 per cent).
2.	To increase the employability of Syrian, Palestinian and Jordanian youth through the introduction and improvement of entrepreneurship education and mandatory internships in higher education institutions.
3.	To technically prepare and motivate young Syrians, Palestinians and Jordanians for an active role in the future reconstruction of Syria.


Activity 1: Support entrepreneurs

Outcomes:
	Number of Jordanian business support organisation scaled and able to deliver quality services to both existing and new start businesses;
	Number of existing Jordanian businesses scaled to offer job opportunities to beneficiary youth;
	Number of new businesses established by youth: Syrian refugees (25 per cent) vs. Jordanians (75 per cent), this acknowledges the difficulty for Syrians to start a new business in Jordan.
	Number of new businesses that continue operating after two years of being established. (Only measurable after completion of the project, which does not fall within programme period);
	Number of jobs created due to the intervention after two years of establishment. (Only measurable after completion of the project, which does not fall within programme period);

Activity 2: Reinforcing education institutes
Result 2.1 An entrepreneurship programme introduced at 5 partner institutions
Outcomes:
	Number of students enrolled a year from launch in new programmes at partner institutions;
	Per centage increase of participants interested in starting a business after the programme;
	Number of alumni that found employment within 6 months after graduation.

Result 2.2 An internship programme introduced at partner institutions facilitating 500 internships Outcomes
	Number of interns offered a regular contract following their internship;
	Number of internship-alumni that found employment 6 months after fulfilling the internship in the same sector as their internship.

Activity 3: Reconstruction skills training programme
Result 3.1 Scholarship Programme
Outcomes:
	Number of students that obtain employment within 6 months of graduation;
	Per centage increase of participants interested to start a business after graduation;
	Per centage increase of participants in extra-curricular activities engaging in post conflict reconstruction in Syria.
	Per cent age of alumni engaging in post-conflict reconstruction work within 6 months of the end of the programme (in the unlikely even the conflict will be resolved).

Result 3.2. Practice Oriented Training Programme
Outcomes:
	Per centage increase of participants indicating they are interested to engage in post conflict reconstruction in Syria;
	Per centage of alumni engaging in post-conflict reconstruction work within 6 months of the end of the programme (in the unlikely even the conflict will be resolved).
